ast','to speak too proudly or happily about what you have done or what you own:\nHe didn\'t talk about his exam results in case people thought he was boasting.\nParents enjoy boasting about their children\'s achievements.',0),(533,'boat','a small vehicle for travelling on water:\na rowing/sailing boat\na fishing boat\nWe took turns to row the boat up the river.\n \nJackF/iStock/Getty Images Plus/GettyImages',0),(534,'body','the whole physical structure that forms a person or animal:\nA good diet and plenty of exercise will help you to keep your body healthy.\nShe rubbed suncream over her entire body.',0),(535,'boil','to reach, or cause something to reach, the temperature at which a liquid starts to turn into a gas:\nLiquid nitrogen boils at a very low temperature.\nShe scalded herself on some boiling water.\nIf you give water to a small baby to drink, you have to boil it first.',0),(536,'bold','not frightened of danger:\nShe was a bold and fearless climber.\nThe newspaper made the bold move/took the bold step of publishing the names of the men involved.',0),(538,'bombing','an attack or attacks on a place or area using bombs, or the activity of attacking in this way:\nHeavy bombing has gutted the city.\nThere was a wave of bombings in the south of the country.',0),(539,'bone','any of the hard parts inside a human or animal that make up its frame:\nThe child was so thin that you could see her bones.\nhuman/animal bones\n \nSCIEPRO/Science Photo Library/GettyImages',0),(540,'bonus','an extra amount of money that is given to you as a present or reward for good work as well as the money you were expecting:\na productivity bonus\na Christmas bonus\nThe company used to give discretionary bonus payments.',0),(541,'book','a written text that can be published in printed or electronic form:\nHave you read any good books recently?\nHe has a new book out (= published).\nShe wrote a book on car maintenance.\n \nhudiemm/E /GettyImages',0),(542,'booking','an arrangement you make to